CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 28, 1953, pg. 17 reads: "Posing For TV...Preceding the program for the birthday party, TV and candid camera fans took slews of pictures of the guest of honor and visitors...this shot are Toki Schalk Johnson, women's editor of the Courier; Mrs. Burrell K. Johnson, long-time friend of the honoree; Mrs. Vann, Mrs. Nell G. Dressler, vice chairman of the Republican party of Allegheny County; Judge Hobson R. Reynolds of Philadelphia, and Mrs. Nina Mack of Detroit."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Toki Schalk Johnson, Mrs. Burrell K. Johnson, Jessie Vann, Nell G. Dressler, Judge Hobson R. Reynolds, and Nina Mack, standing in Penn Sheraton hotel for Jessie Vann's birthday party
